{"key":"post-6165424","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6165424</id>\n<content>You can use any stiff wire.  A bread tie would not hold the bag sealed well.  Steel bailing wire is available at any hardware store.  If you live near a small airport, you can get stainless steel safety wire for ten bucks a roll.  That's what I use, and the ties can be used over and over again.  You could also use plastic zip ties intended for electrical wires.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6165606</next>\n<prev>6165415</prev>\n<first>6163988</first>\n<last>6167103</last>\n<when>1160759088</when>\n<utime>10/13/06 08:04 PM</utime>\n</post>"}